    color: #000000;&lt;br&gt;
}&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Hello {!Contact.FirstName},&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Thank you for contacting Harman Customer Support.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Bluetooth, in a perfect environment, will perform well for up to 30 feet.  However, walls, obstacles, and other wireless devices can impede that 30-foot range.  If it works well at 10 feet or less, it is likely that there is something interfering with your wireless Bluetooth signal, causing these dropouts&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Another possibility is that sometimes a Bluetooth connection can become corrupt. Try the following steps to unpair and re-repair your Bluetooth connection. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Forget/unpair the headphones on your device.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Perform manual pairing. (x&lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;font size =5&gt;[List Steps Here]&lt;/font size&gt;&lt;/font color&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If this doesn’t solve the issue, we need to determine if the problem is in the device or the headphones. Try to connect the headphones to a different device (phone/tablet/music player) to see if it fixes the problem.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If the issue is still not resolved, the last thing to try is a reset.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt; RESET will wipe all previous settings and pairings, so it will be necessary to pair your unit with your devices again.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
To reset, (x&lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;font size =5&gt;[List Steps Here]&lt;/font size&gt;&lt;/font color&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If this does not solve the problem, please continue to &lt;b&gt;“Next Steps”&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="color: red"&gt;&lt;font size =5&gt;[insert appropriate NEXT STEPS template here]&lt;/font size&gt;&lt;/font color&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;i&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Note: For your reference, your case number is {!Case.CaseNumber}.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Regards,&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;{!User.FirstName}&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;{!User.Title}&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;The HARMAN Customer Experience Team&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;style type="text/css"&gt;
