Hello {!Contact.FirstName},&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Thank you for contacting Harman Customer Support.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
There are 3 potential causes for a problem like this.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Dust/Dirt/Debris blocking the ear tip screen&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Balance Control in your source device, music player app, or headphone app (if applicable)&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Left & Right earbud sync issue&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Cleaning The Eartips&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
This is the most common reason for no sound/lack of sound issues. A simple cleaning will almost always fix this problem. &lt;a href="https://support.jbl.com/us/en/howto/tws-headphones-re-establishing-volume-levels-us/000017775.html"&gt;Please click on this link for detailed online instructions.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
You may also check out these videos for best practices on how to keep your &lt;a href="https://support.jbl.com/us/en/product-support/headphones-support-guide.html#video1"&gt;True Wireless (TWS) headphones&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://support.jbl.com/us/en/product-support/headphones-support-guide.html#video2"&gt;In-Ear headphones&lt;/a&gt; at their best sound performance.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Checking Balance Control&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If cleaning doesn't solve the problem, the next thing to check is the balance control. This allows you to make one side louder than the other. Be sure that the left/right balance control is set to default (centered).&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Check the balance control on your source device by going to the "Accessibility" settings. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Check the balance control on your music player app, commonly found in the playback or EQ settings.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Check the balance control on the JBL Headphone or One App. &lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;font size =5&gt;*ONLY INCLUDE THIS IF THE PRODUCT IS COMPATIBLE WITH THE APP*&lt;/font size&gt;&lt;/font color&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
L/R Eartip Sync Issue&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
The two earpieces should normally be connected together without issue. However, sometimes wireless interference may cause corruption between the connection of the two earpieces, causing one earpiece not to produce any sound.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Forget/unpair the headphones on your device.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Manually pair the two earpieces together. &lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;font size =5&gt;[Provide the steps that can be found in the manual]&lt;/font size&gt;&lt;/font color&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Pair the headphones with your device and see if this resolves your problem.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Reset &lt;br&gt;
&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
