Your headphones utilize a feature called "Check My Best Fit" in the Headphones App. This feature will determine if you are using the correct ear tip size and the positioning within the ear canal. Please go to or download the JBL Headphones App, scroll down to "Check My Best Fit", and click to begin the process. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Once you have accomplished a tight seal, if you still feel that the bass is lacking, another feature within the app is Personi-Fi. This is a quick test that enables the headphones to perfectly match your hearing capabilities. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href="https://support.jbl.com/us/en/howto/personi-fi-2-0-us/000040242.html"&gt;Click here for instructions on how to set up Personi-Fi.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If you're still not satisfied with the results after completing the Personi-Fi setup, there are 3 other potential causes for a problem like this.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
The sonic quality of your source, depending on what you are listening to&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
EQ Settings&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Source Device&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;If it is lacking bass sometimes…&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
We need to determine the common denominator. For example, if it only happens on a certain album, you may want to adjust the EQ to boost the bass a little bit while listening to that album. But if it only happens when you are using a specific streaming service or app, you might want to check with the service or app to improve the sonic quality. However, if it appears to be completely random, try boosting the low-frequency settings in the EQ to find a happy medium so that a typical recording sounds more full, but recordings with extreme bass are not excessive. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If this does not solve the problem, please continue to &lt;b&gt;“Next Steps”&lt;/b&gt;. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;If it is always lacking bass regardless of the source or song…&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
This means that the problem is not with the source material. Please try the following steps in order to determine the problem. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If using an EQ, try turning it off to see if it fixes the problem. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If not using an EQ, try turning it on and boosting the bass a little bit. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
To determine if the problem is in the source device, try connecting the earbuds to a different device (phone/tablet/music player/etc.). &lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
As a last resort, please try resetting the earbuds. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt; RESET will wipe all previous settings and pairings, so it will be necessary to pair your unit with your devices again.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
To reset, (x&lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;font size =5&gt;[List Steps Here]&lt;/font size&gt;&lt;/font color&gt;)&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If none of these steps fix the issue, it is possible that the earbuds, by design, may not be able to provide enough bass to your liking. You may want to go with an in-ear that will provide more bass. &lt;br&gt;
