Hello {!Contact.FirstName},&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Thank you for contacting Harman Customer Support.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
In order for the headphones to give you the best audio response, you must create a tight seal within your ear canal. Please try the following, in order: &lt;br&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Angle the eartip slightly downward to make it easier to insert into your ear canal.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Gently twist the earbud to fit it securely into the shape of your ear.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Continue twisting the earbud into your ear canal to achieve the best seal and secure fit.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
It is best to try this with all of the provided eartip sizes, until you find the one that accomplishes this most easily.  Once you've done this a few times, it becomes very easy to do every time you put them in your ear.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If you have accomplished a tight seal, but still feel that the volume is imbalanced, this means that there are 3 potential causes for a problem like this.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Dust/Dirt/Debris blocking the ear tip screen&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Balance Control in your source device, music player app, or headphone app (if applicable)&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Source Device&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Cleaning The Eartips&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
This is the most common reason for no sound/lack of sound issues. A simple cleaning will almost always fix this problem. &lt;a href="https://support.jbl.com/us/en/howto/tws-headphones-re-establishing-volume-levels-us/000017775.html"&gt;Please click on this link for detailed online instructions.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
You may also check out these videos for best practices on how to keep your &lt;a href="https://support.jbl.com/us/en/product-support/headphones-support-guide.html#video1"&gt;True Wireless (TWS) headphones&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://support.jbl.com/us/en/product-support/headphones-support-guide.html#video2"&gt;In-Ear headphones&lt;/a&gt; at their best sound performance.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Checking Balance Control&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If cleaning doesn't solve the problem, the next thing to check is the balance control. This allows you to make one side louder than the other. Be sure that the left/right balance control is set to default (centered).&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Check the balance control on your source device by going to the "Accessibility" settings. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Check the balance control on your music player app, commonly found in the playback or EQ settings. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Check the balance control on the JBL Headphone or One App. &lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;font size =5&gt;*ONLY INCLUDE THIS IF THE PRODUCT IS COMPATIBLE WITH THE APP*&lt;/font size&gt;&lt;/font color&gt;)&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Different Source Device&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 40px;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If cleaning doesn’t solve the issue, we need to determine if the problem is in the device or the headphones. Try to connect the headphones to a different device (phone/tablet/music player) to see if it fixes the problem. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If this does not solve the problem, please continue to “&lt;b&gt;Next Steps&lt;/b&gt;”&lt;br&gt;
