&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
There are 5 potential causes for a problem like this.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Line of sight&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Electrical Interference&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Wireless Interference&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Corrupt Bluetooth connection&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Source device issues&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
First, Bluetooth, in a perfect environment, will perform well for up to 30 feet.  However, walls, obstacles, and other wireless devices can impede that 30-foot range.  If it works well at 10 feet or less, it is likely that there is something interfering with your wireless Bluetooth signal, causing these dropouts. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Items like Microwaves, Refrigerators, and other powerful electric products can cause interference. Try getting away from these items, including going outside, if necessary, to see if this fixes the problem.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Routers can also cause interference. Most are smart enough to find the cleanest signal when they boot up. Try shutting down your router, waiting 30 seconds, and booting it up again to see if it fixes the problem.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Another possibility is that sometimes a Bluetooth connection can become corrupt. Try the following steps to unpair and re-repair your Bluetooth connection.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Forget/Unpair the speaker on your device.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Perform manual pairing. (x&lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;font size =5&gt;[List Steps Here]&lt;/font size&gt;&lt;/font color&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If this doesn’t solve the issue, we need to determine if the problem is in the device or the speaker. Try to connect the speaker to a different device (phone/tablet/music player, etc.) to see if it fixes the problem.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If the issue is still not resolved, the last thing to try is a reset. Reset may fix the issue, much in the way rebooting a computer or phone fixes many problems.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
