&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
There are 3 potential causes for a problem like this.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Volume level conflict between the source device and speaker&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Corrupt Bluetooth connection&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Source device issue&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Please try the following steps in order to determine the problem. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Bluetooth can work in 2 ways.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Absolute Volume:&lt;/b&gt; This means that when you adjust the volume on your device, you can also see the volume adjusting on the speaker, and vice-versa. One volume control between the two. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Independent Volume:&lt;/b&gt; This means that your device and speaker volume controls are independent of each other.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Many devices now default to Absolute Volume, but can be changed to Independent Volume in the device settings. If your device is currently set to Independent Volume, it is possible that one or both of the volume settings are set too low to give you adequate volume.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Try adjusting the device volume to 75%-100% and adjust the volume of the speaker to your desired level.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Sometimes a Bluetooth connection can become corrupt. To determine if this is the case, forget/unpair the speaker on your device and perform manual pairing. (x&lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;font size =5&gt;[List Steps Here]&lt;/font size&gt;&lt;/font color&gt;)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
To determine if the problem is in the source device or the speaker, try connecting the speaker to a different device (phone/tablet/music player/etc.)&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Reset may fix the issue, much in the way rebooting a computer or phone fixes many problems.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt; RESET will wipe all previous settings and pairings, so it will be necessary to pair your unit with your devices again.&lt;br&gt;
