Source Device&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If the volume changes (aka pumping) only occurs as the volume is increased to loud levels, this means the unit is working by design. As the internal amplifier reaches its limits, an internal limiter engages in order to protect itself from damage. There is no way to bypass this. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If the speaker cannot play loud enough to your liking, you may want to consider a bigger, more powerful speaker.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
